		&=		\alpha\beta\big(\rho_1(c) - \rho_2(c)\big)^2.
	\end{align*}
	Hence $\rho_1(c)=\rho_2(c)$, for all $c\in A_{sa}$, so $\rho_1=\rho_2$ and we conclude
	that $\rho$ is a pure state. 
\end{proof}




